class_notes:
All Latin 102 sections have tiered enrollment; additional spaces will be added to the course with each round of enrollment in order to give all students a better opportunity to enroll in the Latin 102 section of their choice for Spring 2022.
Questions about enrollment in Latin sections should be directed to our Classics Undergraduate Degree Program Coordinator Ms. Kim Oliphant (kmoliph@emory.edu); she will work with appropriate faculty to address your questions/concerns. Some issues cannot be addressed until pre-registration has ended for all students.
For all intermediate Greek and Latin sections:
Questions about enrollment in intermediate and advanced Greek and Latin courses, including concerns about course conflicts, should be directed to our Classics Undergraduate Degree Program Coordinator Ms. Kim Oliphant (kmoliph@emory.edu); she will work with appropriate faculty to address your questions/concerns. Some issues cannot be addressed until pre-registration has ended for all students.
course_description: Continuation of Latin 101. Further study of Latin forms and syntax, followed by reading from one or more authors.
